%S A394658 56,135,375,686
%N A394658 Numbers k such that sigma(k) = psi(k) + tau(k) + Omega(k)^2.
%C A394658 a(5) > 10^10, if it exists. - _Amiram Eldar_, Mar 28 2026
%e A394658 56 is a term since sigma(56) = 120 = 96 + 8 + 4^2 = psi(56) + tau(56) + Omega(56)^2.
%o A394658 (PARI) isok(k) = {my(f = factor(k)); sigma(f) == prod(i=1, #f~, (f[i, 1]+1) * f[i, 1]^(f[i, 2]-1)) + numdiv(f) + bigomega(f)^2; } \\ _Amiram Eldar_, Mar 27 2026
